<item>
            <title>[LU-1023] strange numbers shown in obdfilter-survey</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1023</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m testing lustre-2.1.54 and quick ran obdfilter-survey on it. The obdfilter-survey could run, but some numbers are strange and some numbers are not working well. (same results on current master branch)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is obdfilter_survey_&amp;lt;date&amp;gt;_&amp;lt;hostname&amp;gt;.summary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mon Jan 23 12:07:10 JST 2012 Obdfilter-survey for case=disk from dl02&lt;br/&gt;
ost  1 sz 100663296K rsz 1024K obj    2 thr  128 write  714.81             ERROR read 1319.86             ERROR &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It always shows ERROR for min and max value, because stats&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; in global values in obdfilter_survey_&amp;lt;date&amp;gt;_&amp;lt;hostname&amp;gt;.detail is always -1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And, here is obdfilter_survey_&amp;lt;date&amp;gt;_&amp;lt;hostname&amp;gt;.detail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;126/128 Total: 637.928552/second&lt;br/&gt;
126/128 Total: 662.950942/second&lt;br/&gt;
126/128 Total: 564.928819/second&lt;br/&gt;
126/128 Total: 698.904949/second&lt;br/&gt;
128/128 Total: 696.935185/second&lt;br/&gt;
119/128 Total: 686.928559/second&lt;br/&gt;
Total: total 98304 threads 128 sec 0.000000 inf/second&lt;br/&gt;
=============&amp;gt; write global&lt;br/&gt;
-1 564.928819 828.885614&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;difftime (start and end) is zero(0.000000) and return infinity of thread per second, because divided by zero.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, I saw some very strange numbers on the detail log file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;128/128 Total: 805.908932/second&lt;br/&gt;
124/128 Total: 827.918036/second&lt;br/&gt;
128/128 Total: 851.893513/second&lt;br/&gt;
128/128 Total: 3098.609575/second&lt;br/&gt;
               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^&lt;br/&gt;
128/128 Total: 798.896942/second&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;during the test, it sometimes shows unreasonable numbers above.&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
